<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871228-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Oshman's Accord Terminated</HL><DD> 12/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OSHMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Oshman's Sporting Goods Inc. said it terminated its agreement in principle to sell substantially all the assets of its Abercrombie andamp; Fitch division to an investor group headed by Michel Zelnik.    The sporting goods retailer said it plans to pursue sale of the division to another potential purchaser. The division has a book value of about $15 million.    In New York, Mr. Zelnik, an apparel executive, said in a statement that he and his investment group withdrew their offer for Abercrombie andamp; Fitch &quot;in light of recent market conditions and the outlook for retailing.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>